This paper deals with bibliometric measures and mathematical models for estimating the h-index, which are commonly used in the field of computer science. The paper also discusses statistical modeling and prediction of the h-index. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
